-- EU’s Lewandowski Sees Need for Jobs Investment, Stuttgarter Says
-- B y   N a o m i   K r e s g e
-- 2012-01-25T18:02:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-25/eu-s-lewandowski-sees-need-for-jobs-investment-stuttgarter-says.html
Austerity alone won’t be enough to
address the euro crisis without “public investment to
revitalize the jobs market,”  Stuttgarter Zeitung  quoted Janusz Lewandowski, the European Union budget commissioner, as saying
in an interview.  Demand has been created due to cuts to public spending, the
newspaper cited Lewandowski as saying in an e-mailed preview of
an interview to be published tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Naomi Kresge in Berlin at 
 nkresge@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at 
 pserafino@bloomberg.net  